HEADWORD: Scutelliplantar
<hw>Scu*tel`li*plan"tar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>scutellus</ets> a shield + <ets>planta</ets> foot.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having broad scutella on the front, and small
scales on the posterior side, of the tarsus; -- said of certain
birds.</def>⟦br⟧
